<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id91218e0c-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s9226"><num value="9226">§ 9226.</num><heading> Travel sanctions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of State may deny a visa to, and the Secretary of Homeland Security may deny entry into the United States of, any alien who is—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id91218e0d-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s9226/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> a designated person;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id91218e0e-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s9226/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> a corporate officer of a designated person; or</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id91218e0f-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s9226/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> a principal shareholder with a controlling interest in a designated person.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id91218e10-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/pl/114/122/tII/s206">Pub. L. 114–122, title II, § 206</ref>, <date date="2016-02-18">Feb. 18, 2016</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/130/108">130 Stat. 108</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
